subject: Adding zlib-devel dependency for llvm-devel
commitMessage:
Adding zlib-devel dependency for llvm-devel

RPM is not capable of detection dependencies for llvm-devel, as they are inside
llvm-config tool, not usual pkg-config files.

Current llvm-devel will not be usable without zlib-devel and produces an error
/usr/lib64/gcc/x86_64-tizen-linux/4.9/../../../../x86_64-tizen-linux/bin/ld: cannot find -lz

Minor fix: clang libstdc++ name. Library provides tag libstdc++-4.9 not libstdc++49

Change-Id: I11f332ba78e7164cf37716673386dde13ff8304a
Signed-off-by: Vyacheslav Barinov <v.barinov@samsung.com>
